7. Why is it useful?

Very useful in

• Bit Manipulation
• Bit Masks
• Flags
• Embedded Programming
• Networking
• Device Drivers
• Operating Systems

Instead of writing

int mask = 170;

Write

int mask = 0b10101010;

Now the bit pattern is immediately visible.

-----------------------------------------

8. Example - Bit Mask

#include <iostream>
using namespace std;

int main()
{
    int mask = 0b00001111;

    cout << mask;

    return 0;
}

Output

15

-----------------------------------------

9. Example - Bitwise AND

#include <iostream>
using namespace std;

int main()
{
    int a = 0b1010;
    int b = 0b1100;

    cout << (a & b);

    return 0;
}

Calculation

1010

1100

----

1000

Output

8

