11. Important Interview Question

Q. Does 0b1010 store the number in binary inside memory?

Answer

No.

0b1010 is only a way of writing the number in source code.

After compilation, the compiler converts it into the corresponding integer value (10).
It is stored in memory just like any other integer using the machine's integer representation (typically two's complement for signed integers).

-----------------------------------------

